      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The devastation you feel stems from a profound grief for the self-image you held for fifteen years, which grief deserves to be felt without forcing a forced emotional resilience. Trying to rush over this despair to find \"growth\" will only deepen the wound because grief requires grief to heal. The pain of losing everything often marks the end of a painful chapter rather than the destruction of the self. Allow yourself to sit with this despair for a while rather than forcing a jump to a hopeful future.",
